techno-blast.effectText: If the user is holding a appropriate plate or drive, the damage inflicted will match it.
techno-blast.flavorText:
The user fires a beam of light at
its target. The type changes depending
on the Drive the user holds.

tectonic-rage--physical.name: tectonic-rage--physical
tectonic-rage--physical.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
tectonic-rage--physical.flavorText:
The user burrows deep into the ground and slams
into the target with the full force of its Z-Power.
The power varies, depending on the original move.

tectonic-rage--special.name: tectonic-rage--special
tectonic-rage--special.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

teeter-dance.name: teeter-dance
teeter-dance.flavorText:
Confuses all POKéMON on
the scene.

telekinesis.name: telekinesis
telekinesis.effectText: Moves have 100% accuracy against the target for three turns.
telekinesis.flavorText:
The user makes the target float with its
psychic power. The target is easier to
hit for three turns.

teleport.name: teleport
teleport.effectText: Immediately ends wild battles.  No effect otherwise.
teleport.flavorText:
A move for fleeing
from battle.

temper-flare.name: temper-flare
temper-flare.flavorText: Spurred by desperation, the user attacks the target. This move's power is doubled if the user's previous move failed.

tera-blast.name: tera-blast
tera-blast.flavorText: If the user has Terastallized, it unleashes energy of its Tera Type. This move inflicts damage using the Attack or Sp. Atk stat—whichever is higher for the user.

tera-starstorm.name: tera-starstorm
tera-starstorm.flavorText: With the power of its crystals, the user bombards and eliminates the target. When used by Terapagos in its Stellar Form, this move damages all opposing Pokémon.

terrain-pulse.name: terrain-pulse
terrain-pulse.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
terrain-pulse.flavorText:
The user utilizes the power of the terrain to attack.
This move’s type and power changes depending on
the terrain when it’s used.

thief.name: thief
thief.flavorText:
While attacking, it may
steal the foe’s held item.

machineItem.name: TM23
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

thousand-arrows.name: thousand-arrows
thousand-arrows.effectText: Grounds the target, and hits even Flying-type or levitating Pokémon.
thousand-arrows.flavorText:
This move also hits opposing Pokémon
that are in the air. Those Pokémon are
knocked down to the ground.

thousand-waves.name: thousand-waves
thousand-waves.effectText: Prevents the target from leaving battle.
thousand-waves.flavorText:
The user attacks with a wave
that crawls along the ground.
Those hit can’t flee from battle.

thrash.name: thrash
thrash.effectText: Hits every turn for 2-3 turns, then confuses the user.

throat-chop.name: throat-chop
throat-chop.effectText: Prevents the target from using sound-based moves for two turns.
throat-chop.flavorText:
The user attacks the target’s throat, and the
resultant suffering prevents the target from using
moves that emit sound for two turns.

machineItem.name: TR95
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

thunder.name: thunder
thunder.effectText: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target.
thunder.flavorText:
An attack that may
cause paralysis.

machineItem.name: TR09
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

thunder-cage.name: thunder-cage
thunder-cage.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
thunder-cage.flavorText:
The user traps the target in a cage of sparking
electricity for four to five turns.

thunder-fang.name: thunder-fang
thunder-fang.effectText: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target and a 10% chance to make the target flinch.
thunder-fang.flavorText:
The user bites with
electrified fangs.
It may also make the
foe flinch or become
paralyzed.

machineItem.name: TM66
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

thunder-punch.name: thunder-punch
thunder-punch.effectText: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.
thunder-punch.flavorText:
An electric punch.
It may paralyze.

machineItem.name: TM05
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

thunder-shock.name: thunder-shock
thunder-shock.effectText: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.
thunder-shock.flavorText:
An electrical attack that
may paralyze the foe.

thunder-wave.name: thunder-wave
thunder-wave.flavorText:
A move that may
cause paralysis.

machineItem.name: TM14
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

thunderbolt.name: thunderbolt
thunderbolt.effectText: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.
thunderbolt.flavorText:
An attack that may
cause paralysis.

machineItem.name: TR08
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

thunderclap.name: thunderclap
thunderclap.flavorText: This move enables the user to attack first with a jolt of electricity. This move fails if the target is not readying an attack.

thunderous-kick.name: thunderous-kick
thunderous-kick.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
thunderous-kick.flavorText:
The user overwhelms the target with lightning-like
movement before delivering a kick. This also lowers
the target’s Defense stat.

tickle.name: tickle
tickle.effectText: Lowers the target’s Attack and Defense by one stage.
tickle.flavorText:
Makes the foe laugh to
lower ATTACK and DEFENSE.

tidy-up.name: tidy-up
tidy-up.flavorText: The user tidies up and removes the effects of Spikes, Stealth Rock, Sticky Web, Toxic Spikes, and Substitute. This also boosts the user’s Attack and Speed stats.

topsy-turvy.name: topsy-turvy
topsy-turvy.flavorText:
All stat changes affecting the target
turn topsy-turvy and become the
opposite of what they were.

torch-song.name: torch-song
torch-song.flavorText: The user blows out raging flames as if singing a song, scorching the target. This also boosts the user's Sp. Atk stat.

torment.name: torment
torment.effectText: Prevents the target from using the same move twice in a row.
torment.flavorText:
Torments the foe and stops
successive use of a move.

toxic.name: toxic
toxic.effectText: Badly poisons the target, inflicting more damage every turn.
toxic.flavorText:
A poison move with
increasing damage.

toxic-spikes.name: toxic-spikes
toxic-spikes.effectText: Scatters poisoned spikes, poisoning opposing Pokémon that switch in.
toxic-spikes.flavorText:
The user lays a trap
of poison spikes at
the foe’s feet. They
poison foes that
switch into battle.

machineItem.name: TR54
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

toxic-thread.name: toxic-thread
toxic-thread.effectText: Poisons the target and lowers its Speed by one stage.
toxic-thread.flavorText:
The user shoots poisonous threads to poison the
target and lower the target’s Speed stat.

trailblaze.name: trailblaze
trailblaze.flavorText: The user attacks suddenly as if leaping out from tall grass. The user's nimble footwork boosts its Speed stat.

transform.name: transform
transform.effectText: User becomes a copy of the target until it leaves battle.
transform.flavorText:
The user assumes
the foe's guise.

tri-attack.name: tri-attack
tri-attack.effectText: Has a 20% chance to burn, freeze, or paralyze the target.
tri-attack.flavorText:
Fires three kinds
of beams at once.

machineItem.name: TR19
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

trick.name: trick
trick.flavorText:
Tricks the foe into trading
held items.

machineItem.name: TR38
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

trick-or-treat.name: trick-or-treat
trick-or-treat.effectText: Adds ghost to the target’s types.
trick-or-treat.flavorText:
The user takes the target trick-or-treating.
This adds Ghost type to the target’s type.

trick-room.name: trick-room
trick-room.effectText: For five turns, slower Pokémon will act before faster Pokémon.
trick-room.flavorText:
The user creates a
bizarre area in which
slower Pokémon get
to move first for five
turns.

machineItem.name: TM70
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

triple-arrows.name: triple-arrows
triple-arrows.flavorText: The user delivers an axe kick, then fires three arrows. This raises the chance of its future attacks landing critical hits and also lowers the target's defensive stats.

triple-axel.name: triple-axel
triple-axel.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
triple-axel.flavorText:
A consecutive three-kick attack that becomes more
powerful with each successful hit.

triple-dive.name: triple-dive
triple-dive.flavorText: The user performs a perfectly timed triple dive, hitting the target with splashes of water three times in a row.

triple-kick.name: triple-kick
triple-kick.effectText: Hits three times, increasing power by 100% with each successful hit.
triple-kick.flavorText:
Hits three times
with rising power.

trop-kick.name: trop-kick
trop-kick.effectText: Lowers the target’s Attack by one stage after inflicting damage.
trop-kick.flavorText:
The user lands an intense kick of tropical origins on
the target. This also lowers the target’s Attack stat.

trump-card.name: trump-card
trump-card.effectText: Power increases when this move has less PP, up to a maximum of 200.
trump-card.flavorText:
The fewer PP this
move has, the more
power it has for
attack.

twin-beam.name: twin-beam
twin-beam.flavorText: The user shoots mystical beams from its eyes to inflict damage. The target is hit twice in a row.

twineedle.name: twineedle
twineedle.effectText: Hits twice in the same turn.  Has a 20% chance to poison the target.
twineedle.flavorText:
Jabs the foe twice
using stingers.

twinkle-tackle--physical.name: twinkle-tackle--physical
twinkle-tackle--physical.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
twinkle-tackle--physical.flavorText:
The user creates a very charming space using its
Z-Power and totally toys with the target. The power
varies, depending on the original move.

twinkle-tackle--special.name: twinkle-tackle--special
twinkle-tackle--special.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

twister.name: twister
twister.effectText: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.
twister.flavorText:
Whips up a tornado
to attack.

u-turn.name: u-turn
u-turn.effectText: User must switch out after attacking.
u-turn.flavorText:
After making its
attack, the user
rushes back to switch
places with a party
Pokémon in waiting.

machineItem.name: TM56
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

upper-hand.name: upper-hand
upper-hand.flavorText: The user reacts to the target's movement and strikes with the heel of its palm, making the target flinch. This move fails if the target is not readying a priority move.

uproar.name: uproar
uproar.effectText: Forced to use this move for several turns.  Pokémon cannot fall asleep in that time.
uproar.flavorText:
Causes an uproar for 2 to 5
turns and prevents sleep.

machineItem.name: TR35
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

v-create.name: v-create
v-create.effectText: Lowers the user’s Defense, Special Defense, and Speed by one stage each.
v-create.flavorText:
With a hot flame on its forehead, the user
hurls itself at its target. It lowers the
user’s Defense, Sp. Def, and Speed stats.

vacuum-wave.name: vacuum-wave
vacuum-wave.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
vacuum-wave.flavorText:
The user whirls its
fists to send a wave
of pure vacuum at
the foe. This move
always goes first.

veevee-volley.name: veevee-volley
veevee-volley.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
veevee-volley.flavorText:
The more Eevee loves its Trainer, the greater the
move’s power. It never misses.

venom-drench.name: venom-drench
venom-drench.effectText: Lowers the target’s Attack, Special Attack, and Speed by one stage if it is poisoned.
venom-drench.flavorText:
Opposing Pokémon are drenched in an odd
poisonous liquid. This lowers the Attack,
Sp. Atk, and Speed stats of a poisoned target.

machineItem.name: TR91
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

venoshock.name: venoshock
venoshock.effectText: Inflicts double damage if the target is Poisoned.
venoshock.flavorText:
The user drenches the target in a special
poisonous liquid. Its power is doubled
if the target is poisoned.

machineItem.name: TM74
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

vice-grip.name: vice-grip
vice-grip.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

victory-dance.name: victory-dance
victory-dance.flavorText: The user performs a dance to usher in victory. This raises the user’s offensive and defensive stats and increases the damage dealt by the user’s moves by 50 percent.

vine-whip.name: vine-whip
vine-whip.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
vine-whip.flavorText:
Whips the foe with
slender vines.

volt-switch.name: volt-switch
volt-switch.effectText: User must switch out after attacking.
volt-switch.flavorText:
After making its attack, the user
rushes back to switch places with
a party Pokémon in waiting.

machineItem.name: TM80
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

volt-tackle.name: volt-tackle
volt-tackle.effectText: User takes 1/3 the damage inflicted in recoil.  Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.
volt-tackle.flavorText:
A life-risking tackle that
slightly hurts the user.

wake-up-slap.name: wake-up-slap
wake-up-slap.effectText: If the target is asleep, has double power and wakes it up.
wake-up-slap.flavorText:
This attack inflicts
high damage on a
sleeping foe. It
also wakes the foe
up, however.

water-gun.name: water-gun
water-gun.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

water-pledge.name: water-pledge
water-pledge.effectText: With Grass Pledge, halves opposing Pokémon’s Speed for four turns.
water-pledge.flavorText:
A column of water strikes the target. When
combined with its fire equivalent, the
damage increases and a rainbow appears.

water-pulse.name: water-pulse
water-pulse.effectText: Has a 20% chance to confuse the target.
water-pulse.flavorText:
Attacks with ultrasonic
waves. May confuse the foe

water-shuriken.name: water-shuriken
water-shuriken.flavorText:
The user hits the target with throwing
stars two to five times in a row.
This move always goes first.

water-sport.name: water-sport
water-sport.flavorText:
The user becomes soaked to
raise resistance to fire.

water-spout.name: water-spout
water-spout.effectText: Inflicts more damage when the user has more HP remaining, with a maximum of 150 power.
water-spout.flavorText:
Inflicts more damage if the
user’s HP is high.

waterfall.name: waterfall
waterfall.effectText: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.

machineItem.name: TR16
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

wave-crash.name: wave-crash
wave-crash.flavorText: The user shrouds itself in water and slams into the target with its whole body to inflict damage. This also damages the user and raises the user’s action speed.

weather-ball.name: weather-ball
weather-ball.effectText: If there be weather, this move has doubled power and the weather’s type.
weather-ball.flavorText:
The move’s type and power
change with the weather.

machineItem.name: TM46
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

whirlpool.name: whirlpool
whirlpool.effectText: Prevents the target from leaving battle and inflicts 1/16 its max HP in damage for 2-5 turns.

machineItem.name: TM36
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

whirlwind.name: whirlwind
whirlwind.effectText: Immediately ends wild battles.  Forces trainers to switch Pokémon.
whirlwind.flavorText:
Blows away the foe
& ends battle.

wicked-blow.name: wicked-blow
wicked-blow.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
wicked-blow.flavorText:
The user, having mastered the Dark style, strikes the
target with a fierce blow. This attack always results
in a critical hit.

wide-guard.name: wide-guard
wide-guard.effectText: Prevents any multi-target moves from hitting friendly Pokémon this turn.
wide-guard.flavorText:
The user and its allies are protected from
wide-ranging attacks for one turn. If used
in succession, its chance of failing rises.

wild-charge.name: wild-charge
wild-charge.effectText: User receives 1/4 the damage it inflicts in recoil.
wild-charge.flavorText:
The user shrouds itself in electricity
and smashes into its target.
It also damages the user a little.

machineItem.name: TR86
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

wildbolt-storm.name: wildbolt-storm
wildbolt-storm.flavorText: The user summons a thunderous tempest and savagely attacks with lightning and wind. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

will-o-wisp.name: will-o-wisp
will-o-wisp.flavorText:
Inflicts a burn on the foe
with intense fire.

machineItem.name: TM38
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

wing-attack.name: wing-attack
wing-attack.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.

wish.name: wish
wish.effectText: User will recover half its max HP at the end of the next turn.
wish.flavorText:
A wish that restores HP.
It takes time to work.

withdraw.name: withdraw
withdraw.effectText: Raises the user’s Defense by one stage.

wonder-room.name: wonder-room
wonder-room.effectText: All Pokémon’s Defense and Special Defense are swapped for 5 turns.
wonder-room.flavorText:
The user creates a bizarre area in which
Pokémon’s Defense and Sp. Def
stats are swapped for five turns.

machineItem.name: TM71
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

wood-hammer.name: wood-hammer
wood-hammer.effectText: User receives 1/3 the damage inflicted in recoil.
wood-hammer.flavorText:
The user slams its
rugged body into the
foe to attack. The
user also sustains
serious damage.

work-up.name: work-up
work-up.effectText: Raises the user’s Attack and Special Attack by one stage each.
work-up.flavorText:
The user is roused, and its Attack
and Sp. Atk stats increase.

machineItem.name: TR85
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

worry-seed.name: worry-seed
worry-seed.effectText: Changes the target’s ability to Insomnia.
worry-seed.flavorText:
A seed that causes
worry is planted on
the foe. It prevents
sleep by making its
ability Insomnia.

wrap.name: wrap
wrap.effectText: Prevents the target from fleeing and inflicts damage for 2-5 turns.

wring-out.name: wring-out
wring-out.effectText: Power increases against targets with more HP remaining, up to a maximum of 121 power.
wring-out.flavorText:
The user powerfully
wrings the foe.
The more HP the foe
has, the greater this
attack’s power.

x-scissor.name: x-scissor
x-scissor.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
x-scissor.flavorText:
The user slashes at
the foe by crossing
its scythes or claws
as if they were a pair
of scissors.

machineItem.name: TR60
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

yawn.name: yawn
yawn.effectText: Target sleeps at the end of the next turn.
yawn.flavorText:
Lulls the foe into yawning,
then sleeping next turn.

zap-cannon.name: zap-cannon
zap-cannon.effectText: Has a 100% chance to paralyze the target.

zen-headbutt.name: zen-headbutt
zen-headbutt.effectText: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.
zen-headbutt.flavorText:
The user focuses its
willpower to its head
and rams the foe.
It may also make the
target flinch.

machineItem.name: TR69
machineItem.descriptionPtBr: Uma máquina técnica que ensina um movimento a um Pokémon compatível.

zing-zap.name: zing-zap
zing-zap.effectText: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.
zing-zap.flavorText:
A strong electric blast crashes down on the target,
giving it an electric shock. This may also make the
target flinch.

zippy-zap.name: zippy-zap
zippy-zap.effectText: Inflicts regular damage with no additional effect.
zippy-zap.flavorText:
The user attacks the target with bursts of electricity
at high speed. This move always goes first and results
in a critical hit.
